<< Data type conversion (int to float,bool,string) >>
int ===> float str  bool
float ===> int bool str
bool ===> int float str
str ===> int bool float

print("senthil Assignment March 12")
'''
int ===> float str  bool
float ===> int bool str
bool ===> int float str
str ===> int bool float
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1841565/valueerror-invalid-literal-for-int-with-base-10

This means you cannot convert a floating-point number in a string to an integer. 
In addition, you cannot convert letters to an integer 
(unless you are using letters with a special meaning, like “inf”).
https://careerkarma.com/blog/python-valueerror-invalid-literal-for-int-with-base-10/
coffee_bags_as_int = int(float(coffee_bags))
'''
x = 1 # int
y = 2.8 # float
z = "Python" # String
w = True #Boolean
v = "1275998889"

#convert from int to float, string, boolean:
print (" << convert from int to float, string, boolean >>")
a, b, c = float(x), str(x), bool(x)
print(a, b, c)
print(type(a), type(b), type(c))

#convert from int to int, string, boolean:
print (" << convert from float to int, string, boolean >>")
d, e, f = int(y), str(y), bool(y)
print(d, e, f)
print(type(d), type(e), type(f))

#convert from String to int, float, boolean:
print (" << convert from string to int, float, boolean >>")
# String to int, float not possible unless it is a number
g = int(v)
# h = int(z)
# h = float(z)
i = bool(z)
print(g , i)
print(type(i))

#convert from bool to int, float, string:
print (" << convert from boolean to int, string, float >>")
j, k, l = int(w), str(w), float(w)
print(j, k, l)
print(type(j), type(k), type(l))


<< Programs >>
For below programs collect input from user, pi is constant value 3.14 (print output in formatted way)
write a program to calculate perimeter of the circle with radius 10.2
write a program to calculate area of circle with radius (float) (collect using input function)
write a program to calculate perimeter of the cricle with radius (float) (collect it through input function)
Collect radius and height from user,
calculate Area of cone (area of cone = 0.33 * pi * r * r * h) (int)

print ("Input Practise")
pi = 3.14
r = int(float(input("Please enter the radius")))
h = int(float(input("Please enter the height")))
area_of_cone = 0.33 * pi * r * r * h
print(f"area_of_cone :  {area_of_cone}")
print(f"area_of_cone_type :  {type(area_of_cone)}")
